01:00:35,498 --> 01:00:38,434
(cheering and booing)

1050
01:00:38,434 --> 01:00:41,037
(upbeat music)

1051
01:00:48,778 --> 01:00:51,514
(whistle blowing)

1052
01:00:51,514 --> 01:00:54,851
(cheerleaders cheering)

1053
01:01:22,178 --> 01:01:23,312
- [Coach] It's your foot?

1054
01:01:23,312 --> 01:01:24,547
- Yeah.

1055
01:01:24,547 --> 01:01:25,615
- [Coach] Do you think
 you can stand on it?

1056
01:01:25,615 --> 01:01:27,517
- [Jack] I'm not sure.

1057
01:01:27,517 --> 01:01:30,253
- [Coach] I'll have
 to take a look.

1058
01:01:32,822 --> 01:01:34,791
- Ow, ow.

1059
01:01:35,691 --> 01:01:37,927
(applause)

1060
01:02:02,085 --> 01:02:04,487
(whistle blowing)

1061
01:02:04,487 --> 01:02:06,055
- [Jack Voiceover]
  Life is funny.

1062
01:02:06,055 --> 01:02:08,624
One minute, I was running
 to the cheers of the crowd,

1063
01:02:08,624 --> 01:02:10,693
and the next I was being
wheeled down a hall

1064
01:02:10,693 --> 01:02:13,729
on a gurney by my parents
  and their boyfriends.

1065
01:02:13,729 --> 01:02:15,264
- You were playing beautifully.

1066
01:02:18,734 --> 01:02:19,802
- Who belongs to who?

1067
01:02:20,903 --> 01:02:22,672
We can't have a thousand
people back here,

1068
01:02:22,672 --> 01:02:23,773
immediate family only.

1069
01:02:24,874 --> 01:02:26,375
- We're the parents.

1070
01:02:26,375 --> 01:02:28,778
- Pick any two, the rest can
 stay in the waiting room.

1071
01:02:35,284 --> 01:02:36,452
- Who's in charge here?

1072
01:02:38,387 --> 01:02:41,624
Well, there's, uh,
  nothing broken,

1073
01:02:42,792 --> 01:02:44,594
but you do have a
  very bad sprain.

1074
01:02:44,594 --> 01:02:47,597
I'd like to have an air
  cast and crutches, please.

1075
01:02:47,597 --> 01:02:50,700
Now, I'd like you to keep
  this elevated tonight

1076
01:02:50,700 --> 01:02:52,268
and all day tomorrow.

1077
01:02:52,268 --> 01:02:55,538
I want you to have ice on it
 30 minutes out of every hour.

1078
01:02:55,538 --> 01:02:57,573
Any problems, give me a call.

1079
01:02:57,573 --> 01:02:59,675
- What about basketball?

1080
01:02:59,675 --> 01:03:02,411
- Well, I think you better
 learn to walk before you run.

1081
01:03:09,685 --> 01:03:12,155
- Maybe we shouldn't have
  all gone to the game.

1082
01:03:12,155 --> 01:03:14,724
Maybe it ruined
 your concentration.

1083
01:03:14,724 --> 01:03:16,259
- It's not your fault.

1084
01:03:16,259 --> 01:03:19,662
My leg just got tangled with
 the other guy's, that's it.

1085
01:03:21,430 --> 01:03:23,299
- Hey, kiddo, you got messages.

1086
01:03:23,299 --> 01:03:25,268
Your coach, Maggie, and Elaine.

1087
01:03:25,268 --> 01:03:26,936
She said she'll come over
  during the day tomorrow

1088
01:03:26,936 --> 01:03:28,571
and hang out with you
  while everyone's at work.

1089
01:03:28,571 --> 01:03:29,772
- Oh that's so nice.

1090
01:03:29,772 --> 01:03:30,606
She adores you.

1091
01:03:31,474 --> 01:03:32,975
She thinks you're very special.

1092
01:03:34,210 --> 01:03:35,711
- I am very special.

1093
01:03:35,711 --> 01:03:38,881
- I know, but it's nice when
 someone else agrees with you.

1094
01:03:43,653 --> 01:03:44,487
- Mom?

1095
01:03:44,487 --> 01:03:46,022
- Mm?

1096
01:03:46,022 --> 01:03:49,559
- What's it mean when your
father picks a boring boyfriend?

1097
01:03:49,559 --> 01:03:52,328
- That he had a lapse
 in judgment after us.

1098
01:03:52,328 --> 01:03:56,699
- That's what I thought.

1099
01:03:58,834 --> 01:03:59,669
- Enough?

1100
01:03:59,669 --> 01:04:00,469
- Thank you.

1101
01:04:00,469 --> 01:04:01,637
- You're welcome.

1102
01:04:05,241 --> 01:04:08,010
(birds chirping)

1103
01:04:15,218 --> 01:04:16,285
- You look very pale.

1104
01:04:17,353 --> 01:04:18,321
- I feel very pale.

1105
01:04:19,422 --> 01:04:20,756
- Do you want another pill?

1106
01:04:20,756 --> 01:04:21,591
- No thanks.

1107
01:04:23,025 --> 01:04:25,161
- [Jack Voiceover] If she
  hadn't been Mrs. Burka,

1108
01:04:25,161 --> 01:04:28,064
Max's mother, I would
  have asked her to do that

1109
01:04:28,064 --> 01:04:30,066
to my whole body
  for hours on end.

1110
01:04:31,500 --> 01:04:33,569
I wondered if she knew how
  she was making me feel.

1111
01:04:35,104 --> 01:04:36,005
- That feels good.

1112
01:04:38,808 --> 01:04:40,776
- Well, I better run.

1113
01:04:42,078 --> 01:04:45,248
I told Steve I'd be
 home, and you know how

1114
01:04:45,248 --> 01:04:47,049
he gets if everything
 isn't perfect.

1115
01:04:49,318 --> 01:04:50,586
You rest a while longer, okay?

1116
01:04:50,586 --> 01:04:52,088
Your mom's gonna be home soon.

1117
01:05:03,099 --> 01:05:05,835
(birds chirping)

1118
01:05:08,404 --> 01:05:09,939
- Oh, hey.

1119
01:05:09,939 --> 01:05:12,575
- So, are you like down
for the count or what?

1120
01:05:12,575 --> 01:05:13,676
- Down, but not out

1121
01:05:15,011 --> 01:05:16,912
- Hey, well, I
 brought you a present.

1122
01:05:16,912 --> 01:05:18,047
- Yeah, what, homework?

1123
01:05:19,081 --> 01:05:19,915
- Ta-da.

1124
01:05:21,417 --> 01:05:22,251
- Hi.

1125
01:05:24,453 --> 01:05:25,688
- Hi.

1126
01:05:25,688 --> 01:05:26,956
- I hope you're not out.

1127
01:05:26,956 --> 01:05:28,624
I'm really looking
  forward to Friday.

1128
01:05:28,624 --> 01:05:30,326
I assume you're still free?

1129
01:05:30,326 --> 01:05:32,028
- Free but crippled.

1130
01:05:32,028 --> 01:05:33,929
- Well, what's happening Friday?

1131
01:05:34,930 --> 01:05:35,765
- We have a date.

1132
01:05:36,699 --> 01:05:37,667
- Really?

1133
01:05:37,667 --> 01:05:39,402
Well, uh, can I come?

1134
01:05:39,402 --> 01:05:41,704
- No, Max, because then
it wouldn't be a date.

1135
01:05:42,905 --> 01:05:45,808
- Anyways, I'm gonna be
late, piano lesson day.

1136
01:05:53,582 --> 01:05:55,851
(soft music)

1137
01:05:55,851 --> 01:05:56,986
- Did you see that?

1138
01:05:56,986 --> 01:05:58,688
She just kissed you.

1139
01:05:58,688 --> 01:06:00,690
That's like the second
time in recent history.

1140
01:06:01,624 --> 01:06:03,159
Well this is better than TV.

1141
01:06:03,159 --> 01:06:04,927
I'm watching you
 go through puberty.

1142
01:06:12,101 --> 01:06:14,804
- So, uh, what do
  you do in a Zendo?

1143
01:06:16,706 --> 01:06:18,307
Just sit and wait?

1144
01:06:19,742 --> 01:06:21,110
- No waiting, just sitting.

1145
01:06:23,012 --> 01:06:24,380
- And then what?

1146
01:06:24,380 --> 01:06:25,214
- Nothing.

1147
01:06:27,149 --> 01:06:28,384
- I don't get it.

1148
01:06:28,384 --> 01:06:30,486
- Well there's nothing
to get, nothing happens.

1149
01:06:31,587 --> 01:06:33,556
But if you do it enough,
you get yourself.

1150
01:06:36,992 --> 01:06:37,827
- Okay.

1151
01:06:42,998 --> 01:06:45,401
(soft music)

1152
01:06:57,747 --> 01:07:00,883
- [Jack] So how many times
  have you seen that film?

1153
01:07:00,883 --> 01:07:01,817
- Like two million.

1154
01:07:02,918 --> 01:07:03,753
- Yeah.

1155
01:07:05,221 --> 01:07:07,323
My dad used to take me to
  the movies every Saturday.

1156
01:07:07,323 --> 01:07:09,325
- Mine did too, maybe it's like

1157
01:07:09,325 --> 01:07:10,793
a gay dad thing or something.

1158
01:07:13,529 --> 01:07:14,363
I'm kidding.

1159
01:07:18,534 --> 01:07:20,803
- So is it better or
 worse to be a girl

1160
01:07:20,803 --> 01:07:22,171
or a guy with a gay dad?

1161
01:07:24,240 --> 01:07:26,575
- I think it's worse for a guy.

1162
01:07:26,575 --> 01:07:28,611
It's more threatening or
something, I don't know.

1163
01:07:28,611 --> 01:07:30,980
- Yeah, I have to say,
 when he first told me,

1164
01:07:30,980 --> 01:07:33,182
I kept thinking, Does
 that mean I'm gay too?

1165
01:07:34,283 --> 01:07:35,117
- And now?

1166
01:07:37,586 --> 01:07:39,155
- Oh, now I'm sure I'm not gay.

1167
01:07:44,960 --> 01:07:47,062
So how come you never
 talk about your mom?

1168
01:07:48,898 --> 01:07:50,232
- Because she's not around.

1169
01:07:51,534 --> 01:07:52,468
- Is she dead?

1170
01:07:53,903 --> 01:07:55,304
- No, she lives in Virginia.

1171
01:07:57,807 --> 01:08:01,277
Three years ago, she invited
 me to come and visit,

1172
01:08:01,277 --> 01:08:04,814
and I remember I spent the
  whole summer baby-sitting

1173
01:08:04,814 --> 01:08:07,716
her two new kids while she
  went off with her friends

1174
01:08:07,716 --> 01:08:08,851
and got her nails done.

1175
01:08:11,387 --> 01:08:14,190
She's got a new
 life, a new husband,

1176
01:08:15,524 --> 01:08:17,126
and as far as she's concerned,
 my dad and I are just

1177
01:08:17,126 --> 01:08:18,828
mistakes she made
  a long time ago.

1178
01:08:19,795 --> 01:08:21,530
- But she's your mom, right?

1179
01:08:21,530 --> 01:08:22,364
- Yeah.

1180
01:08:24,066 --> 01:08:25,968
Then she got annoyed about
  something, threw her stuff

1181
01:08:25,968 --> 01:08:27,203
in the back of a car and,

1182
01:08:28,304 --> 01:08:29,138
never came back.

1183
01:08:30,806 --> 01:08:32,208
- How old were you?

1184
01:08:32,208 --> 01:08:33,008
- Six.

1185
01:08:34,977 --> 01:08:38,714
And I remember, I
thought it was my fault,

1186
01:08:38,714 --> 01:08:41,917
like I thought I had
 done something wrong.

1187
01:08:41,917 --> 01:08:43,686
- Yeah, I thought
  I was too boring.

1188
01:08:54,597 --> 01:08:55,464
Good night.

1189
01:08:55,464 --> 01:08:56,365
- Can you get out?

1190
01:08:56,365 --> 01:08:57,666
- I can try.

1191
01:08:57,666 --> 01:08:59,902
(giggling)

1192
01:09:03,272 --> 01:09:04,106
- Thank you.

1193
01:09:04,106 --> 01:09:04,974
- Welcome.

1194
01:09:04,974 --> 01:09:06,242
- [Michael] Hey.

1195
01:09:06,242 --> 01:09:08,511
- Sorry about that, we
 just started talking.

1196
01:09:08,511 --> 01:09:10,412
- Oh, that's all right.

1197
01:09:10,412 --> 01:09:12,515
So you want me to drive
you guys somewhere

1198
01:09:12,515 --> 01:09:14,116
where you can make
  out or something?

1199
01:09:15,284 --> 01:09:17,052
- Michael, it's our
 first date, okay?

1200
01:09:18,187 --> 01:09:19,488
- Geez, kids today,
you're damned if you do,

1201
01:09:19,488 --> 01:09:20,489
damned if you don't.

1202
01:09:21,790 --> 01:09:23,359
- Sorry about that.

1203
01:09:23,359 --> 01:09:24,360
- Thank you.

1204
01:09:29,098 --> 01:09:31,667
(car starting)

1205
01:09:40,976 --> 01:09:41,810
- Thank you.

1206
01:09:41,810 --> 01:09:42,645
- You're welcome.

1207
01:09:44,980 --> 01:09:48,684
- So, um, I guess I'll
 phone you tomorrow.

1208
01:09:48,684 --> 01:09:49,618
- Okay.

1209
01:09:49,618 --> 01:09:50,686
- [Maggie] Okay, thank you.

1210
01:09:50,686 --> 01:09:51,520
- Bye.

1211
01:09:51,520 --> 01:09:52,354
- [Maggie] Bye.

1212
01:10:00,930 --> 01:10:01,764
- So?

1213
01:10:02,932 --> 01:10:05,834
- Well, if I'd known
 dating was that easy,

1214
01:10:05,834 --> 01:10:07,703
I woulda started
 when I was like two.

1215
01:10:12,274 --> 01:10:14,944
We watched the film,
 I held her hand,

1216
01:10:14,944 --> 01:10:19,214
and her hand was sweaty,
and my hand was sweaty,

1217
01:10:19,214 --> 01:10:21,383
and our sweat just
  kind of mixed.

1218
01:10:23,185 --> 01:10:25,254
And then we had ice cream,

1219
01:10:25,254 --> 01:10:27,590
and the vanilla melted
with the chocolate, and,

1220
01:10:30,259 --> 01:10:31,961
it was all just
  kind of fantastic.

1221
01:10:34,063 --> 01:10:35,564
- Yeah, I'll bet it was.

1222
01:10:35,564 --> 01:10:38,167
(car starting)

1223
01:10:42,204 --> 01:10:43,038
- You got enough warm clothes?

1224
01:10:43,038 --> 01:10:43,872
- Yeah.

1225
01:10:43,872 --> 01:10:44,707
- You got money?

1226
01:10:44,707 --> 01:10:46,008
- Yep.

1227
01:10:46,008 --> 01:10:47,309
- It was very nice of
 Elaine to invite you.

1228
01:10:47,309 --> 01:10:48,210
- Yeah, I know, I'm
 Max's entertainment.

1229
01:10:49,778 --> 01:10:50,679
- Have a good time.

1230
01:10:50,679 --> 01:10:52,248
- [Jack] Bye.

1231
01:10:52,248 --> 01:10:53,082
- Bye.

1232
01:11:02,391 --> 01:11:03,792
(tires squealing)

1233
01:11:03,792 --> 01:11:05,561
(horn honking)

1234
01:11:05,561 --> 01:11:06,495
- If someone could
  read the signs,

1235
01:11:06,495 --> 01:11:07,630
we'd know where to get off.

1236
01:11:09,431 --> 01:11:12,568
- Steve, this is not my
 fault, you're driving the car.

1237
01:11:12,568 --> 01:11:13,669
- That's what you say.

1238
01:11:15,437 --> 01:11:18,240
- [Jack Voiceover] Something
 about Mr. Burka swerving

1239
01:11:18,240 --> 01:11:19,642
made me think of Mr. Bailey.

1240
01:11:20,843 --> 01:11:23,045
Swerving on a highway
 was definitely not

1241
01:11:23,045 --> 01:11:25,547
a Mr. Bailey thing to do.

1242
01:11:25,547 --> 01:11:28,651
Made me think of him asking,
 Had my parents crashed?

1243
01:11:48,871 --> 01:11:50,339
- [Elaine] Dinner with
  Uncle Morris and Aunt Mary

1244
01:11:50,339 --> 01:11:52,675
is 7:30, and they're looking
 forward to seeing you.

1245
01:11:52,675 --> 01:11:55,244
- [Steve] Did they write
  seeing you or soaking you?

1246
01:11:55,244 --> 01:11:56,078
Every time we go out
 to dinner with them,

1247
01:11:56,078 --> 01:11:57,913
I have to pay the check.

1248
01:11:57,913 --> 01:12:00,149
- [Elaine] So just decide
  that this time you won't.

1249
01:12:04,420 --> 01:12:05,421
- [Steve] I grew
up on this lake.

1250
01:12:05,421 --> 01:12:06,889
I bet you didn't
know that, Jack.

1251
01:12:06,889 --> 01:12:09,358
Almost drowned in
  this bad boy once.

1252
01:12:09,358 --> 01:12:10,959
- [Max] Every year,
 he tells us about

1253
01:12:10,959 --> 01:12:12,761
how he almost drowned.

1254
01:12:12,761 --> 01:12:13,996
- [Steve] You know,
 it means something

1255
01:12:13,996 --> 01:12:15,931
to have a place to come back to

1256
01:12:15,931 --> 01:12:18,500
- People always feel the
  need to confess on a lake.

1257
01:12:19,601 --> 01:12:21,603
I myself don't
 like lakes anymore.

1258
01:12:21,603 --> 01:12:23,272
They're overrated.

1259
01:12:23,272 --> 01:12:25,140
- Boy, this is the life, huh?

1260
01:12:25,140 --> 01:12:27,309
Million miles away
  from everything.

1261
01:12:27,309 --> 01:12:28,343
- Million years away.

1262
01:12:29,445 --> 01:12:31,080
- No littering please.

1263
01:12:31,080 --> 01:12:32,715
- Feeding the fish.

1264
01:12:32,715 --> 01:12:34,516
- Hey, Captain,
 toss me those chips.

1265
01:12:37,119 --> 01:12:39,421
- [Sam] What's a
  lake made out of?

1266
01:12:39,421 --> 01:12:42,091
- [Elaine] Oh, a lake's
  like a really big puddle.

1267
01:12:42,091 --> 01:12:44,660
- [Sam] Well, what's a
 mountain made out of?

1268
01:12:44,660 --> 01:12:46,495
- [Elaine] Mountain's
 like a big rock.

1269
01:12:46,495 --> 01:12:48,263
- [Sam] Do rocks grow?

1270
01:12:48,263 --> 01:12:50,065
- [Max] Only in your head.

1271
01:12:50,065 --> 01:12:50,899
- [Elaine] Max.

1272
01:12:52,835 --> 01:12:55,170
(murmuring)

1273
01:12:56,572 --> 01:12:58,040
- Uh, could I have
  some more ketchup?

1274
01:12:59,441 --> 01:13:01,844
(murmuring)

1275
01:13:01,844 --> 01:13:04,480
- Hey, Honey, can I get
a refill here, thanks?

1276
01:13:05,314 --> 01:13:06,348
- Any time of day.

1277
01:13:06,348 --> 01:13:09,284
We've called him on emergencies.

1278
01:13:09,284 --> 01:13:11,620
- So, how goes it in the market?

1279
01:13:11,620 --> 01:13:12,454
Any tips?

1280
01:13:13,388 --> 01:13:15,023
- No tips.

1281
01:13:15,023 --> 01:13:17,392
Only top-secret insight
I'm not privy to share.

1282
01:13:23,332 --> 01:13:25,234
What do I owe you
 for Mary and myself?

1283
01:13:26,401 --> 01:13:28,771
- It's okay, Morris,
 we'll split it 50-50.

1284
01:13:28,771 --> 01:13:30,606
- But they've got
 three extra people.

1285
01:13:33,609 --> 01:13:35,744
- In the morning, I want you
 all to come down to the house,

1286
01:13:35,744 --> 01:13:37,846
and I'll make you up
 a nice big breakfast.

