01:40:38,766 --> 01:40:40,934
My life was my own now,
  and my job was to make it

1791
01:40:40,934 --> 01:40:42,236
what I wanted it to be.

1792
01:40:43,670 --> 01:40:46,039
I only wished I'd known
 that a couple of years ago.

1793
01:40:47,541 --> 01:40:51,478
I was Jack, plain Jack, Jack
 out there all by myself.

1794
01:40:59,286 --> 01:41:01,989
(dramatic music)

1795
01:41:04,625 --> 01:41:07,828
Jack takes the pass,
 the announcer's voice

1796
01:41:07,828 --> 01:41:09,430
boomed in my head.

1797
01:41:09,430 --> 01:41:11,565
I ran unevenly across the court,

1798
01:41:11,565 --> 01:41:14,168
wondering if my leg would
  ever be normal again.

1799
01:41:14,168 --> 01:41:17,037
Or if my life would
 ever be normal again.

1800
01:41:17,037 --> 01:41:18,705
Fast Jack is coming in low.

1801
01:41:19,840 --> 01:41:22,109
I crouched down,
 dancing in and out.

1802
01:41:22,109 --> 01:41:24,378
My leg felt like I was
 stepping on pushpins.

1803
01:41:25,813 --> 01:41:28,549
(dramatic music)

1804
01:41:40,527 --> 01:41:43,564
He's up, Fast Jack is up.

1805
01:41:43,564 --> 01:41:44,865
I pushed through the pain.

1806
01:41:46,066 --> 01:41:48,635
As the crowd roared,
 my leg didn't hurt.

1807
01:41:48,635 --> 01:41:51,105
Nothing hurt, my
  mind was flowing.

1808
01:41:52,306 --> 01:41:54,475
I was Fast Jack, and
 I knew I would make it

1809
01:41:54,475 --> 01:41:57,311
and that everything
 would be okay.

1810
01:42:02,316 --> 01:42:04,918
(upbeat music)

